# Notas de Crédito / Devoluciones — Implementation Plan

The existing `returnSlice` handles stock restoration and marks sales as CANCELLED.
This sprint extends it to also generate a **Nota de Crédito (NC-001)** and optionally apply a **credit balance** to the client's account, which can then be used in the next sale in the POS.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Database (Supabase SQL)

```sql
-- 1. Add credit_balance to clients
ALTER TABLE clients ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS credit_balance NUMERIC(10,2) DEFAULT 0;

-- 2. Rename returns -> credit_notes with extra fields (or add columns to returns)
ALTER TABLE returns
  ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS nc_number     TEXT,
  ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS option        TEXT DEFAULT 'REEMBOLSO'  -- 'CREDIT' | 'REEMBOLSO'
    CHECK (option IN ('CREDIT', 'REEMBOLSO')),
  ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS client_id     UUID REFERENCES clients(id);

-- 3. Add a sequence for NC numbering
CREATE SEQUENCE IF NOT EXISTS nc_number_seq START 1;
```

